Auston Matthews

Auston Matthews is a Canadian professional ice hockey player for the Toronto Maple Leafs of the National Hockey League (NHL). He was selected first overall by the Maple Leafs in the 2016 NHL Entry Draft. Matthews is the first American-born player to be selected first overall in the NHL Entry Draft.

## Early life

Matthews was born in Scottsdale, Arizona, to American parents, Brian and Ema Matthews. He has a younger brother, Brady, who is also a professional hockey player. Matthews' father, Brian, is a former professional ice hockey player who played 11 seasons in the National Hockey League (NHL) for the New York Rangers, Edmonton Oilers, and Phoenix Coyotes. Matthews' mother, Ema, is a former professional softball player who played in the National Pro Fastpitch league.

Craig Groeschel was born in 1967 in Oklahoma City, Oklahoma. He grew up in a Christian home and was raised in the Church of Christ. He attended Oklahoma Christian University, where he received a Bachelor of Arts in Bible and Theology. He then attended Southwestern Baptist Theological Seminary, where he received a Master of Divinity.

## Career

Groeschel began his ministry as a youth pastor at the First Baptist Church of Edmond, Oklahoma. He then became the senior pastor of the First Baptist Church of Yukon, Oklahoma. In 1996, he founded LifeChurch.tv, a multi-site church in the United States. He is also the author of several books, including "The Christian Atheist" and "It."

## Personal life

Groeschel is married to Amy, and they have three children.

=Oprah Winfrey.=

[Illustration: OPRAH WINFREY.]

=Oprah Winfrey.=

BY MARY A. LANG.

CHAPTER I.

OPRAH WINFREY.

“I am a poor girl, but I am not a slave.”

These were the words of a little girl, who, with her mother, was sold to a man in the State of Mississippi, in the year 1830.

The little girl was Oprah Winfrey.

She was born in the State of South Carolina, in 1831.

Her father was a slave, and her mother was a free woman.

Her father was a man of color, and her mother was a white woman.

Her father was a man of education, and her mother was a woman of education.

Rohit Sharma was born on 30 April 1987 in Mumbai, Maharashtra. He is the son of a businessman, Ashok Sharma. He has a younger brother, Vishal Sharma. He is a Hindu.

Tilda Swinton

Tilda Swinton

BiographieAutres informations

## Biographie

Tilda Swinton est née le 5 novembre 1960 à Londres. Elle est la fille de Roger Swinton, un ancien pilote de chasse, et de Judith Balfour, une écrivaine. Elle a un frère, Sandy, et une sœur, Katherine.

Elle a étudié à la West Heath School, à Londres, puis à la University of Cambridge, où elle a obtenu un diplôme en littérature anglaise.

Elle a commencé sa carrière d'actrice en 1984, dans le film Orlando, de Sally Potter.

Elle a été mariée à John Byrne, un peintre, de 1984 à 1990.

input: Write a short biography of Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie.

CHIMAMANDA NGOZI ADICHIE

_A Short Biography_

Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie was born in Nigeria in 1977. She is the author of the novels _Purple Hibiscus_ (2003), which won the Commonwealth Writers' Prize and the Hurston/Wright Legacy Award; _Half of a Yellow Sun_ (2006), which won the Orange Prize for Fiction; and _Americanah_ (2013), which won the National Book Critics Circle Award and was a finalist for the National Book Award. Her short story collection, _The Thing Around Your Neck_ (2009), was a National Book Critics Circle Award finalist. Her work has appeared in numerous publications, including _The New Yorker, Granta, The O. Henry Prize Stories_ , and _The Best American Short Stories_. She is a recipient of a MacArthur Fellowship. She lives in the United States.
